narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This Spanish course was great and I would definitely recommend taking this professor's course. Professor Ramos-Ruano was apassionate, though at times somewhat crazy, instructor who taught the course well and made the class more interesting than honestly I thought a Spanish course could be. She also seemed to genuinely cares about how students did in the class, which created a very good class environment.

I would say that the course covers a lot of material over a short period of time, but the textbook and instructor make it doable and enjoyable. I'd recommend the class to another student because I feel more confident in my Spanish now than I did at the beginning of the semester.
